{
  "schema_version": "1.0",
  "description": "Availability window policies define what a specific instructor/location/resource window permits. They do not define course duration; course_consumption_rules.json owns course consumption requirements.",
  "invariants": [
    "A 4-hour availability window must not automatically become two 2-hour slots or multiple shorter appointments.",
    "The inventory resolver may subdivide a window only when both the course consumption rule and the window policy allow it.",
    "Fallback course families require manual approval when fallback_requires_manual_approval is true.",
    "capacity_mode is a policy shortcut; explicit window fields may override mode defaults."
